			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Bandit sashes are a great way to rack up skill if you are between lvl 10-17, after that they are decent for the loot.  For instance, West Karanas Bandit Farm.  There is a nice spawn rate for 2-3 Bandits and a pair of farmers.  If you hang out here you can gather a few of these sashes and turn them into a lad outside of the Pally guild for XP, a bronze weapon, and some $$$.  One can make about 30pp or more depending on the amount of time they spend at one of these camps.  But be careful.  If you are not of lvl 19+, you need to camp the guys in groups of at least 3, and even then it can be extremely dangerous.  Brigands can often spawn in a Bandit's place, and sometimes 2 of the 3 Bandit spawns turn out to be Druid casters, nailing you for 70+ damage.  I use this quest still to go from the camp to Qeynos trading these in for loot and exp at lvl 19 in order to continue the cash flow for my Fletching.  Yesterday there was a fella who had spent his entire earth day between the Hill camp and the Farm and was carrying 69 sashes on his person.  If you know where to turn them in, sashes are woth 2-5pp each...you do the math.  =)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
