			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				For people level 15-19, hunting in western karanas is gernally a really good place to make nice coin.  Hunt down the bandits and take in all the sashes you've looted, and than bring them to South Qeynos at the paladin guild.  Chesgard is the man you want to give them to.  Now through all this trouble, not only do you get exp for the bandits, you get coin from the bandits, a weapon or shield from Chesgard (that you can sell off for 1-3pp), plus you get good faction with qeynos.  Generally, everytime I go back with my loot, altogether I make about 15pp easy.  G'luck all... =)  <BR>
<BR>
Aiiyla<BR>
Bard of the 16th song<BR>
Mith Marr
				</font>
